<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend existing words:</span> If BODY is on the board, prepending ANTI makes ANTIBODY for 14 points plus all premium squares the extension crosses. Look for nouns ending near the left edge.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo potential:</span> ANTI- creates 7+ letter words easily from common 3-4 letter roots. ANTI+QUE, ANTI+DOTE, ANTI+SOCIAL — all valid bingos worth 50+ bonus points.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold A-N-T-I together:</span> These four common tiles combine with almost any root. If you draw them, resist breaking the set for small plays — the bingo potential is worth the wait.</p>
  </div>
</div>

